{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c4623282-c9f5-44a5-8d47-28d490ef2fbc","content":"I don't have a specialized skill for **analyzing** crash dumps — only for collecting them. However, here's how you can analyze your `.dmp` file:\n\n### Recommended Tools\n\n1. **`dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform, CLI):\n   ```bash\n   dotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n   dotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n   ```\n   Useful commands inside the REPL:\n   - `clrstack` — managed call stack\n   - `pe` — print last exception\n   - `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n   - `threads` — list all threads\n\n2. **WinDbg** (Windows, GUI) — load the dump, then:\n   ```\n   .loadby sos coreclr\n   !pe           (print exception)\n   !clrstack     (managed stack)\n   !threads      (all threads)\n   ```\n\n3. **Visual Studio** (Windows) — open the `.dmp` file directly, click **\"Debug with Managed Only\"**.\n\n### Quick triage steps\n1. Start with `pe` (print exception) to see if an unhandled exception caused the crash.\n2. Use `clrstack` to see where it happened.\n3. Check `threads` to look for deadlocks or thread pool exhaustion.\n\nWould you like me to help you run `dotnet-dump analyze` on the file if it's accessible in this environment?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"794f1124-8310-4ce3-b335-0e5cf5cd2b4e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file and wants to analyze it. Let me look at the available skills to see if any are relevant.\n\nLooking at the available skills:\n- `dump-collect` - This is for **collecting** crash dumps, not analyzing them. The description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\"\n- `dotnet-trace-collect` - For capturing diagnostic artifacts, not analyzing dumps\n- `android-tombstone-symbolication` - For Android tombstone files\n- `apple-crash-symbolication` - For Apple .ips crash logs\n\n\nNone of these are designed for analyzing .dmp files directly. Since I don't have a skill that covers dump analysis, I should guide the user toward the appropriate tools and techniques for their specific scenario.","outputTokens":541,"requestId":"A0C3:39E965:9927C5:BC4616:6A013824"},"id":"398e2ab1-914d-4792-b245-f54a7eca2bc2","timestamp":"2026-05-11T02:00:17.295Z","parentId":"22226616-c150-4428-8d14-8827f3ad53d4"}
